700955f.folder: Eastchester Road & Morris Park Avenue, Bronx, NY
700955f.original_title: Bronx: Eastchester Road - Morris Park Avenue
700955f.text:
Eastchester Road, east side, at Morris Park Avenue, showing the concrete wall erected by the W.P.A. On the right are the tracks of the New York, New Haven and Hartford Railroad.
August 11, 1937
W.P.A. Photo
Five Boroughs Project

700956f-a.folder: Eastchester Road & Morris Park Avenue, Bronx, NY
700956f-a.original_title: Bronx: Eastchester Road - Morris Park Avenue
700956f-a.text:
Eastchester Road, north from Morris Park Ave. The two houses, on
the right, bear Nos. 1890 and 1892.
About 1923.
Joseph P. Day.

701495f-a.folder: Morris Park Avenue & Eastchester Road, Bronx, NY
701495f-a.original_title: Bronx: Morris Park Avenue - Eastchester Road
701495f-a.text:
Morris Park Avenue (newly paved), looking west from Eastchester Road. The thoroughfare was paved by the W.P.A.
March 9, 1937
W. P. A. Photo
Five Boroughs Project
